Chapter 14: The Supreme Tao or the One has Physical and Metaphysical Dimensions 1 We look at it, and we do not see it, and we name it &lsquo;the Uniformity.&rsquo;
We listen to it, and we do not hear it, and we name it &lsquo;the Inaudible.&rsquo;
We try to grasp it, and do not get hold of it, and we name it &lsquo;the Subtle.&rsquo;
With these three qualities, it cannot be made the subject of description; and hence we blend them together and obtain &lsquo;The One&rsquo;.

Chapter 57: The State Should Have Concise but Efficient Laws 1 A state may be ruled by measures of correction. Weapons of war may be used with crafty dexterity. But the kingdom is made one&rsquo;s own only by freedom from action and purpose.
2 The multiplication of prohibitive laws increases the poverty of the people.
The more implements to add to their profit that the people have, the greater disorder is there in the state and clan;
